parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Passenger Seat Occupancy Mat (OC3) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front passenger seat occupancy mat can cause the airbag to not deploy in the event of an accident, potentially leading to injury or death.
symptoms: The SRS airbag light remains illuminated
indicating that the front passenger's side airbag is deactivated. The passenger seat occupancy mat sensor is faulty
and the airbag warning light comes on when a passenger is seated in the passenger seat.

the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
